title: Google\Cloud\Bigtable\V2\Cell
name: Cell
description:
Specifies (some of) the contents of a single row/column/timestamp of a table.

Generated from protobuf message google.bigtable.v2.Cell

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.timestamp_micros
params.description: The cell's stored timestamp, which also uniquely identifies it within its column. Values are always expressed in microseconds, but individual tables may set a coarser granularity to further restrict the allowed values. For example, a table which specifies millisecond granularity will only allow values of timestamp_micros which are multiples of 1000.

params.name: data.value
params.description: The value stored in the cell. May contain any byte string, including the empty string, up to 100MiB in length.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Labels applied to the cell by a [RowFilter][google.bigtable.v2.RowFilter].
